metadata.text1:
Clinical assessment may be carried out if no TCB/lab bilirubin available

Otherwise check TCB/serum bilirubin if clinical suspicion of jaundice
metadata.text2:
- Use jaundice chart here FOR BABIES >38 WEEKS. 
For babies <38 weeks consult alternative charts.  

- Protect the baby's eyes with a mask
- Watch for dehydration- increase fluids by 20ml/kg/day
- Mothers can still breast feed 
- Monitor temperature
- if >exchange transfusion threshold consult Iliff handbook for procedure
metadata.text3:
If jaundiced in first 24 hours:

-Consider sepsis
-Check FBC and reticulocytes
-Direct Coombs test
-Group mother and baby- lab must retain both samples
-Blood film and G6PD

Check bilirubin every 6 hours until it is under the treatment threshold for phototherapy AND stable/falling.
